Comment: Please share some code with us, we won't do your homework for you.

Answer: You can use the function `Dates` to add a year month column in the DataFrame. First import the package.

\begin{code}
using Dates
\end{code}

Then define the function

\begin{code}
add_yearmonth(df) = df[:, :ym] .= Dates.format.(Dates.Date.(df[:dt], "yyyy-mm"),"yyyymm")
\end{code}

Now apply this function to your dataframe

\begin{code}
df1=DataFrame([2003  2004; 5    6])
rename!(df1, :x1 => :dt)
add_yearmonth(df1)
\end{code}

